    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash, then remove 2<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>outer leaves</strong> per person from your<strong> lettuce</strong>, pat dry with kitchen paper and set them aside for serving</p><p>Cut the <strong>inner core[s] </strong>into quarters</p><p>Combine the <strong>diced apple</strong>, <strong>chopped shallot</strong>, <strong>mayo</strong>, <strong>cider vinegar </strong>and<strong> chopped parsley</strong> in a bowl</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, <strong>sugar </strong>and<strong> pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>apple</strong> <strong>remoulade</strong></p>",
